Name Openbook 9.0
Description

OpenBook converts printed documents or graphically displayed text into text format on your PC, using high quality OCR, or optical character recognition technology.
You get the result, both visible on your screen as audibly read text.
Before reading the text, you can choose between two leading text-to-speech software synthesizers.
For the visual presentation you will have a lot of low vision options available.
OpenBook reads the text of your document with high precision. It uses both the Nuance OmniPage as ABBYY FineReader OCR engines to give you the most accurate OCR results, making the scanned result approximates the original text with a minimal margin of error.
The built-in voice synthesis of OpenBook you are using the two built-in text-to-speech software synthesizers: RealSpeak Solo (natural, human sounding voices) of Eloquence (efficient synthetic speech)
Technical features
Automatic column recognition
Integrated speech quality
Text display with low vision options, adjusted according to individual needs: font, size, letter spacing and color, image mask and word mark
Split screen mode, the display between OCR results and original document
Integrated search for text
Braille Support
Can be combined with Pearl portable camera

E30243

Name Sensomath
Description

Mathematics Scripture for blind, visually impaired and sighted users:
Thanks to Senso Math blind and partially sighted pupils can now read and write mathematical formulas in the same Word document as their sighted peers, teachers, parents, ...
Senso Math is an add-in for Microsoft Word 2007 and 2010 which allows instant conversion between mathematical formulas in mathematics braille, the equation editor of Word and Flemish Mathematics Code, while preserving the layout and graphics of the document.
Read, write and edit mathematical formulas in Microsoft Word:
Formulas, written in Braille, are converted automatically by Senso Math to editable graphics in the equation editor and to an editable text-based linear representation: the Flemish Mathematics Code.
Also in the reverse direction, the conversion happens automatically. Formulas that you delineate in Microsoft Word with the equation editor or that you deregister in linear code are perfectly readable on a braille display and editable with braille.
Impaired pupils who work with magnification and don't know Braille, can read formulas with the equation editor but edit very slow and difficult. In the linear mode of Senso Math this is much easier, because the formulas in Flemish Mathematics Code can be typed in the Azerty keyboard.
It is only the blind or visually impaired student who need to use Senso Math formulas to read and write. Seeing teachers and conversion centers can continue to use Microsoft Word the classic way and therefore keys, and create homework, exercises and textbooks on an ordinary PC without additional tools.
The emergence of Senso Math: to reconcile different writing forms:
Until now, it was for blind and partially sighted pupils not evident with mathematical formulas and to share tis in a simple and unambiguous way with sighted teachers, counselors or parents.
A working group of the VLOR (Flemish Education) investigated different notation systems in Europe and found that in addition to the mathematics braille there was also need for a uniform text-based code that could be written with a PC keyboard and was useful by both blind, visually impaired and sighted people. This was the trigger for the development of a new Flemish Mathematics Code.
That new math code was however, like the Braille code, to reconcile with the graphical mathematics quotation handled by psychics.
With the new software Senso Math Sensotec managed a very elegant, easy to use and extremely powerful response to this challenge.
Senso Math brings together the different codes in a Word document. Regardless of the form of writing which mathematical formulas are prepared, they can now be read, edited, written and exchanged by both blind, visually impaired and sighted users.
Benefits in the classroom:
The software makes the following scenarios possible:
The teacher can give blind students a digital copy of a text in Microsoft Word that he made with the math editor. He / she does not have to learn new things.
The student can read the received document to a braille display. He can choose to see mathematics Braille or text-based code.
A blind student who is familiar with the mathematics Braille and a Braille keyboard with his laptop, can enter Braille as before. Senso Math makes it accessible for sighted people using the equation editor, the standard math formulas installed in Microsoft.
The teacher can receive a document from a student and make corrections by using the equation editor.
A student who is not familiar with the mathematics Braille or low vision, can read and write the formulas in the text-based Flemish Mathematics Code.
Visually impaired or blind students, their teachers, parents and counselors use the same document to note the mathematics lessons, to study or to exam.
Conversion Centers only have to deliver textbooks as Word documents, where the formulas are created with the equation editor.
Because no conversion operations are longer required, the student and the teacher can instantly exchange documents, without wasting time, with the same efficiency as the sighted students in the classroom.
Technical data:
Senso Math does not replace a screen reader. To display text and mathematical formula on a braille display and to write with a Braille keyboard you also need a screenreading program next Senso Math.
For Microsoft Word 2007 or 2010.
Senso Math is based on the linear Flemish Mathematics Code as published in 2012 within the VLOR and the Mathematics Braille Code (Van der Mey & Notaert, 1975).

Name Audio Notetaker
Description
  • Audio Notetaker is software to create which also notes, images and color codes can be added sound recordings (classes, meetings, interviews).
    - Students, teachers and professionals can manage their recordings and processing. It offers an alternative to written notes.
    - Sound recordings are displayed as blocks, for a good overview and easy navigation.
    - Use the arrow keys you can jump from one to the other fragment.
    - The software automatically splits the sound file into pieces and bring it up on the screen bars. With these bars you can go to work: you can emphasize the structure by providing, to highlight important sections and removing the less important pieces from them by colors.
    - Unwanted sound clips may be removed.
    - When recording a Skype call, you can then see who said what.
    - Data is recorded using the (built-in) microphone or you can record the system sound on your PC.
    - Presentations is possible and they can be subsequently exported to iTunes.
    - In addition to a sound the user slides (ppt), PDF files or images.
    - References to other documents or information sources via 'additional info' added.
    - Text of a presentation can be copied to the 'extra-Extended Info box.
    - Sorting and search functions are available.
    - Recordings of a voice recorder can be imported. Listen before importing is possible.
    - There is a quick start guide and a manual available.
    - Audio Notetaker is available in a Windows and Mac version. The Windows version requires at least Windows XP. The Mac version requires an Intel processor and Mac OS 10.5.8 Leopard or later.
    - A Dutch version is available. A French and German versions will follow later (end of 2014).

additional information
-odt2braille is a braille converter (converter) which is designed to work with OpenOffice.org (version 3.2 and higher) and LibreOffice. These office suites are not (yet) accessible via speech or Braille display.
-This software is designed primarily for sighted care providers with a view to professional braille production.
-odt2braille is a plug-in, this is an additional software module that adds to the office suite.
-A document that is created from a blank document or a Braille template directed, by odt2braille converted into a braille document. The result can still be proofread before printing. The settings for printing can be extensively adjusted.
-odt2braille user has Dutch and a Dutch Braille table.
-Not all commercially available braille printers are supported. There is currently support for printers from Index, and Braillo Interpoint. Support for various other printers in beta version.
-The program is written for the Windows versions of OpenOffice and LibreOffice and is limited (only conversion) on MacOS.
-The program is localized for a range of languages ??including English and Dutch.
-Braille Conversion for 40 languages??, including Dutch, French, English and German is provided.

Ring : camera OCR module unknown Battery operation: Optional Automatic Language Detection : yes Additional information : MagniLink Voice is a reading device for printing. The emphasis is on simplicity of use . The exterior of the device is covered with a gray fabric removable and washable . On the obliquely forward sloping top are three large buttons : two knobs and a orange square button . On the front is a "handle" which the camera is mounted to a picture of the text to read . Magnilink Voice can be tailored to the user by controlling the reading speed , volume, audio profiles , the voices and the light . It can be read in Dutch or English . Other languages ​​are optional. With SAPI5 support also additional votes from external providers such Acapela/Infovox4 can be used . Poorly loaded documents are also read . All functions of the Magnilink Voice be read . The automatic language recognition multiple languages ​​can be automatically recognized on a leaf. Due to the good depth of focus eg thick books can be read without problem . -The reading machine takes a picture of printed text using a flip camera. Without adequate light, the built-in lighting can be used.

-The maximum scan size is an A4 page.

Description -Machine translation- Main Features: : - Capture system: digital camera - OCR-module: Abby FinReader - Battery: no - Automatic language detection: yes Additional information: : - In Belgium EasyReaderPlus is also sold under the name Retina. There are four versions of the Retina: Basic, Pro, Zoom and Touch. . - The base unit is a narrow and high enclosure with a sloping top. At the top there are seven control buttons en the camera slides via a folding arm into the base unit. This is Retina Basic. . - Retina Pro consists of the base unit with an extra keyboard. The keyboard is used fot advanced features such as save, import (PDF, BMP, JPEG, PNG and TIFF), placing bookmarks, multi-page processing (up to 20 pages per minute) and exporting tect as MP3 sound files. . - Retina Zoom consists of four elements: the base unit, the keyboard, a trackball and a widescreen display. . - On the display the text can be showed enlarged an in different color combinations (max. 64). The text can either be moved horizantally or vertically with the trackball. In the mean time the text is read. . - Retina Touch comes with a touchscreen instead of an ordinary screen. Now you can use your finger to indicate the word where Retina should start to read. . - Text on round objects such as cans can also be read. . - The text is placed in front of the unit and under the camera to then be read. You can listen to the sound via the built-in stereo speakers or a headphone. . - The unit comes standard wtih one language of choice. Each language contains multiple voices. You can choose form 17 languages, of which up to four can be intstalled on the device. The reading unit automatically switches to the appropriate language. . - Includes accessoires: headphone with volume control an a high-contrast mat to position the text under the camera. . - Power supply: 110-240 V - Dimensions base unit: 22 x 12 x 26 cm - Weight base unti: 2,45 kg Producer VISIONAID INTERNATIONAL Great Britain E-mail: sales@visionaid-international.com Suppliers and prices Belgium: Ergra Angels: EUR 1 860 for a Basic language (May 2011, including VAT) Belgium: Integra: EUR 1995-3395 (April 2011, including VAT) Netherlands: Slechtziend.nl: EUR 1,055 for the basic version (April 2011, including VAT)

Main Features:
- Capture system: digital camera
- OCR-module: Abby FinReader
- Battery: no
- Automatic language detection: yes
Additional information:
- In Belgium EasyReaderPlus is also sold under the name Retina. There are four versions of the Retina: Basic, Pro, Zoom and Touch.
- The base unit is a narrow and high enclosure with a sloping top. At the top there are seven control buttons en the camera slides via a folding arm into the base unit. This is Retina Basic.
- Retina Pro consists of the base unit with an extra keyboard. The keyboard is used fot advanced features such as save, import (PDF, BMP, JPEG, PNG and TIFF), placing bookmarks, multi-page processing (up to 20 pages per minute) and exporting tect as MP3 sound files.
- Retina Zoom consists of four elements: the base unit, the keyboard, a trackball and a widescreen display.
- On the display the text can be showed enlarged an in different color combinations (max. 64). The text can either be moved horizantally or vertically with the trackball. In the mean time the text is read.
- Retina Touch comes with a touchscreen instead of an ordinary screen. Now you can use your finger to indicate the word where Retina should start to read.
- Text on round objects such as cans can also be read.
- The text is placed in front of the unit and under the camera to then be read. You can listen to the sound via the built-in stereo speakers or a headphone.
- The unit comes standard wtih one language of choice. Each language contains multiple voices. You can choose form 17 languages, of which up to four can be intstalled on the device. The reading unit automatically switches to the appropriate language.
- Includes accessoires: headphone with volume control an a high-contrast mat to position the text under the camera.
- Power supply: 110-240 V
- Dimensions base unit: 22 x 12 x 26 cm
- Weight base unti: 2,45 kg

Start reading immediately
SARA You can start from the box, without the need for any training or experience necessary. Put simply your book or document on the scan plate and press the scan button. SARA scans and recognizes the text and read it immediately. While you can read the speed and adjust the volume or scroll forward or back. If you want to listen to a detailed text then use the pause and intuitive navigation buttons, for example, per word or per line to read. You can even let the words spellen.Voor assistance during the use of SARA or an explanation of the buttons you press the HELP button. SARA is provided with a concise guide.
Create your own settings
SARA is designed with the practical needs of the user in mind. You can make your own settings for others to read the speed, volume and pitch of SARA's built-Peak Real voice synthesizer. Settings tailored so! SARA can be connected to a computer monitor. For example, if you are sighted in large letters and color simultaneously read. It does not matter whether you read the latest bestseller or the policy of your insurance. SARA makes reading easy.
Characteristics of SARA
CD Player for reading audio books or listening to music.
- Built-in speakers on the front.
- Connection for headset front.
- Power to the rear.
- Microphone jack on the back.
- TV Out connection for viewing scanned documents on a TV.
- VGA out for connecting a computer monitor.
- USB port for connecting a keyboard, mouse or external memory.
- Support for multiple languages.
- Size: 50.8 cm. x 8.89 cm. x 30.48 cm
- 20 GB hard disk drive
- 256 MB RAM, 600 MHz Processor
- 100 to 240 volt power

WHAT IS IT?
A EasyLink is a braille input keyboard for the mobile phone and is also available in Braille output.
FOR WHOM?
Users of accessibility software for the mobile phone (Mobile Speak) the Easy Link for use with the phone and / or reading the information in Braille.

With the EasyLink Braille keyboard, you can now fully operate the phone. All functions are accessible wirelessly. And if the phone is outdated, you can Easy Link simply another phone koppelen.Met Easy Link with Braille output, you can still easily view the text and check spelling.

EasyLink12 keyboard with Braille cells

esys 40 is a portable Braille reading line by 40 cells and integrated Braille keyboard. Multifunction and a design for desktop and for portable use. Has a slot for an SD card for more text files to save. Thanks to Bluetooth technology and communications software, the device also connected to a mobile phone or PDA. You can esys 40 to your IT equipment to fill.
The Braille keyboard with 10 keys, gives you the ability to reproduce all the standard keyboard shortcuts for both types and navigate to your computer, Windows applications, mobile phone and PDA just to use.
Use two joysticks to easily through menus to navigate Microsoft Windows. Use the scroll wheel for faster scrolling through information.
Thanks to the automatic sleep mode esys 40, the autonomy of the battery several days.
TECHNICAL CHARACTERISTICS:
- 40 Braille cells
- 40 cursor routing keys
- Braille keyboard with 10 keys
- 2 navigatiejoysticks
- 4 scroll wheels
- Mini USB
- Bluetooth
- Slot for mini SD card
- Lithium-ion battery
- 20 hours autonomy
- Also rechargeable via compatible Nokia phone charger (5.7 V)
- Bag
- Size: 32.5 cm x 8.6 cm x 2 cm
- Weight: 500 g
APPLICATIONS
* Bluetooth
Connect your esys 40 with any PC, mobile phone and pocket PC equipped with a Bluetooth adapter. In the Bluetooth main menu you can set connection parameters and the device name and PIN change.
* USB
Connect your esys 40 with any PC with a USB port and screen reader. Activate the esys 40 USB mode for the first connection. Make sure the external device a corresponding driver is installed. Scroll through your mini SD card as a removable disk.
* Notepad
Create and edit simple text files. Use basic functions such as "find and replace". Maintain your documents and create an advanced tree of folders. Use the "read" a book or document to read more.
* Calculator
For simple operations and accounting currency. Use the memory to store results.
* Alarm clock
Set different weker sin for each day of the week
* Agenda
Plan meetings, check your schedule in your Week, select a date or event you want bewerken.Informatie will be stored in a text file that you can transfer to your PC.
* Tools
Check the correct operation of your esys 40, test the battery level, the keyboard and braillcelstatus, select an additional language for the software interface, update to the latest software version, ...

Name Clavicom NG
Description

ClavicomNG is the latest version of Clavicom. It is a virtual keyboard that allows text input through a keyboard to the computer. It is sufficient for the user clicks on a letter to make them appear in the editor.
ClavicomNG is fully customizable. The integrated edit mode a user can customize keyboard or a new creation with different keys:
- Characters (letters)
- Phrases
- Last word
- Word prediction
- Shortcuts
- An application
- Noise
- ...
The word prediction suggests words based on a dictionary (in the language desired by the user) and a list of previously entered words.
A virtual mouse is integrated into the ClavicomNG. In this way the user can control the mouse (movement and clicks) through scanning.
The software is fully translatable starting from a simple text file in all desired languages. Currently, the file is available in French and English.
Finally, users can create profiles in which all options are saved and that the keyboard can easily be transferred or exported to another place.
You can download the software for free via the website www.hi-france.org

It's that simple. An efficient MP3, but of high quality, will be sent as an attachment to the e-mail. Your recipient is then only to double click on the Annex to your message heard.
You can use the software for free download via www.waxmail.biz

-A wide range of braille is supported via a serial, USB or Bluetooth connection.
-The Braille display is taken into account on the screen (Physical Braille Mode) for a better understanding of what is asked.
-The braille on the braille display that is controlled, an be made visible in a narrow window on the screen so that a sighted guide / instructor can monitor and provide explanations.
-The level of detail that braille is displayed, can be adjusted in three levels.

Name Mobile Speak for Symbian Phones 248455
Description

Mobile Speak is a screen reader application that you can install on certain mobile phones. It allows you to use the device, even if you can not read the visual screen. Information displayed on the screen is handled by text-to-speech software to synthetic speech output so that you may listen through the speakers of your phone or via a headset. The screen content can be presented in Braille if the mobile phone connections with a braille reading line. Speech and Braille output can simultaneously or independently of each other, are used for the following functions to perform:
- Receive calls and perform, and be informed of missed calls
- Read the identification of a caller when an incoming call, and check the number you have entered before you call
- Manage your contacts and call logs'
- Check the battery status, signal strength, bluetooth settings, and other details of the status
- Create and read text messages (SMS), multimedia messaging (MMS) and e-mail
- Surf the Internet and fill in online forms
- Read different types of files including Microsoft Word and simple text
- Read text by character, word or line
- Plan events and tasks
- Check the date and time
- Set the clock and alarm
- Create text and voice notes
- Perform arithmetic operations
- Convert from one currency or unit of measurement to another
- Listen to stored media files or internet audio streams
- Browse the system files and folders on the phone and memory card
- Configure phone settings, themes, profiles and ringtones
- Assign speed dial keys and voice tags for
- Access to other integrated 3rd-party applications such as Fringe or IM Plus instant messenger, Wallet, and Wayfinder Access for GPS navigation, to name but a few
- Connect to other mobile phones but also laptops and computers to exchange information
Mobile Speak, the software of your phone on, that way you still have access to the built-in functions and applications. In fact, so can compatible 3rd-party programs to install more to do with your mobile phone. External hardware such as Bluetooth keyboards and headsets are also supported similar, so you wireless control over the phone.
More information can be found on the website www.mobilespeak.com

Name Magic 13
Description

Magic is the ideal software solution for visually impaired computer users. It combines powerful magnification capabilities with artificial voice to the screen to read. In Magic you can on the computer screen from 1 to 16 times. Between the increasing opportunities 1 and 2, you can even marginally increase. This means you can choose from increases of eg 1.3 or 1.6. Also you can choose from several ways to increase, so well enlarged and non-enlarged portions of the screen.
The voice capabilities of Magic will help you to process the information on your screen. You can speak text as you type or designates something with the mouse. Magic can also read the full screen where the words are enlarged and / or marked. Magic speech is delivered including the English Peak Real voice synthesizer. There is no separate voice synthesizer bijbesteld be.
The mouse and cursor settings help you to determine the position on the screen. They can choose from several options. This can include self-color and the size of the mouse and cursor set.
With the color settings, use the color on your screen to your own preferences. You can change the colors, your screen in 2 colors (monochrome) and brightness. All these options can even be combined to meet your specific needs are met.
Magic 10.5 English (size: ca 61 Mb) Attention: Not suitable for Windows VISTA
If you have a valid license for Magic 10.5 has this version of Magic 10.5 fully functional. Inien you do not have valid license will serve as a demo version. You will have the full functionality for 40 minutes. If those 40 minutes have passed, you must restart your computer to before you can use Magic again.
Note: This downloadable version contains no English voice synthesizer. If you have an English speech synthesizer, you can use it. Consult the documentation. When you buy Magic Voice is an English speech synthesizer included.
The installation is not translated. After installation, you have an English version of Magic.

Basic Features
-Version: 1.2
-Designed for: Mac OS X
-Magnification range: 1 to 21 times (magnifier) ??and 9 to 240 points font (tekstvergroter)
-Texts with smooth edges: no (magnifier) ??/ yes (tekstvergroter)
-Color adjustment: no (magnifier) ??/ yes (tekstvergroter)
-Image invertible: no (magnifier) ??/ yes (tekstvergroter)
- Higher resolutions supported: yes
Additional information (Title IV 04)
- VisioVoice is a software that provides magnification that is not normally present within the operating system itself. That's a document reader, more visible cursors, a magnifier and mp3 converter.
-When installing VisioVoice asks whether the user is blind or visually impaired. This choice can later be changed.
-VisioVoice has three magnification modes: Tekstvergroter, magnifier and reader.
-magnifier: The user determines the size and location of a window in which an increase is realized of what is happening around the cursor. The cursor or focus in a dialog box is not followed by the magnification.
- Text Magnifier: The user determines the size and location of a window in which an enlargement is realized by the text surrounding the mouse pointer. Also typed text itself is enlarged by a legible font, set between 9 and 240 points.
-The use of 2 monitors are supported.
-Reader: Selected text blocks are read by the reader where the text read aloud highlighted. In addition, the text is shown enlarged and graphic elements can be omitted. For background color, font color and font size : the Reader uses the same settings as the Text magnifier. Fast-forward or rewind within the text is possible.
-Thanks to 'interface saying " everything the mouse points is spoken through the supplied Infovox iVox voice (EN & TC) ,. Also all the keys that are pressed, can be pronounced. The speech is quickly switched off and on by only holding down a key. There can be worked with two different voices, a voice interface and a storytelling voice.
-VisioVoice can be started with the computer.

Name WordTalk
Description

Word Talk is a free text-to-speech plugin developed for use with all versions of Microsoft Word (from Word 97 and later). The program reads the text of a document and mark each time the word read. Talk is also a talking dictionary to help decide which word spelling is correct.
The program appears in your toolbar is highly customizable and allows you to:
- The color of the marker to choose
- The voice and the speed to change
- Text to speech to be converted and stored as a sound file (WAV or MP3) so that the later can be played with an iPod or MP3 player.
Word Talk can only work with SAPI 5 voices (and Microsoft).

Name kReader Mobile
Description

The Mobile Reader product line, developed by knfbReading Technology Inc. places the functionality of a reading machine into a multifunction cell phone.
The Mobile Reader products can be activated and are ready to use with the touch of a single button on the phone. The user takes a photo of the print to be read and the character recognition software, in conjunction with high quality text-to-speech, will read the contents of the document aloud. At the same time, it can display the print on the phone's built-in screen and highlight each word as it is spoken.
Additionally the user can snap pictures and read in several languages as well as translate between languages.
The knfbReader Mobile and kReader Mobile software packages run on a multifunction mobile phone, which allows the user to read mail, receipts, handouts and many other documents wherever the user happens to be. This is a truly pocket-size solution to reading on the go.
The software exists in two versions:
* The knfbReader Mobile software has a feature set which is designed for use by blind or low-vision users.
* The kReader Mobile is an identical software package, but offers add-ons tailor-made for users who have difficulty reading due to learning or language problems.

Name BraillePen 12 Touch/Easylink 12 Touch
Description

Basic Features:
- Number of braille cells : 12
- Area under braille cells : flat
- Braille Keyboard: yes
- Battery operation: yes
- Bluetooth: yes
Additional Information :
- The BraillePen 12 Touch is a compact Braille display with 12 Braille cells and a 6 - point Braille keyboard .
- This compact Braille is known by two names : BraillePen ( manufacturer & Integra ) and EasyLink ( Optelec ) .
- The BraillePen 12 Touch has touch-sensitive cursor routing (Active Touch) .
- In the middle is a mini - joystick for navigation .
- The connection to the laptop , tablet or smartphone is realized via a wireless Bluetooth connection .
- The BraillePen 12 Touch is compatible with various control software for various operating systems: Mobile Peak , Talks & Zoom, Mobile Accessibility , Braille Back, VoiceOver in OS X 10.6 ( Snow Leopard ) and above, VoiceOver in iOS version 4 and higher , Dolphin Pen , Supernova , Window-Eyes and Jaws .
- In addition to the Braille keys and mini - joystick there are various control buttons on the top: shift , space , control and 2 round keys ( keys Pan ) left and right of the Braille cells .
- The device has a built-in rechargeable battery that provides approximately 12 hours of autonomy .
- The BraillePen 12 Touch comes with leather case and battery charger.
- Dimensions : 151 x 96 x 21 mm
- Weight : 260 g

Description

Compact keyboard that is adjusted so that one finger can be operated.

* Compact keyboard, 4 selectable strings, operable with a finger, PS / 2
* Compact keyboard with grill, 4 selectable strings, operable with a finger, PS / 2
* Compact keyboard with grille, operable with a finger, 4 selectable strings, extra buttons caps, PS / 2
* Compact keyboard with 4 selectable strings, extra buttons caps, PS / 2

Name Multi Function Panel
Description -Machine translation- This customizable keyboard was designed for any Windows application, including but not limited to PC gaming and flight simulation. It is also useful as an alternative keyboard. Multi Function Panel (MFP) has the same functionality as a keyboard, with some great benefits. Each key can be removed and relocated at the table where the user wants. Each key is held in place by a re-usable inexhaustible "glue" that allows the keys repeatedly to move, without any adhesive ability to lose. With CH's Control Manager software (included with each unit of CH), CH 16, you can still check players, including multiple MFPs join. as a keyboard, with some great benefits. This customizable keyboard was designed for any Windows application, including but not limited to PC gaming and flight simulation. It is also useful as an alternative keyboard.
Multi Function Panel (MFP) has the same functionality as a keyboard, with some great benefits. Each key can be removed and relocated at the table where the user wants. Each key is held in place by a re-usable inexhaustible "glue" that allows the keys repeatedly to move, without any adhesive ability to lose. With CH's Control Manager software (included with each unit of CH), CH 16, you can still check players, including multiple MFPs join.
Each MFP comes with:
- A panel
- A transparent table
- A set of 25 keys
It is possible for 25 additional buttons to purchase.
